00:09:59.686 --> 00:10:02.296 A:middle
in Xcode 8 [applause].

00:10:04.346 --> 00:10:05.286 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Good morning everyone.

00:10:06.996 --> 00:10:09.436 A:middle
So Joshua's walked us
through the fundamental pieces

00:10:09.486 --> 00:10:11.306 A:middle
that are involved in
signing your applications.

00:10:12.086 --> 00:10:15.806 A:middle
You need a signing certificate
and a provisioning profile

00:10:16.086 --> 00:10:18.516 A:middle
that matches your device
and your app's entitlements.

00:10:19.136 --> 00:10:21.656 A:middle
But many of you also
have app extensions.

00:10:21.896 --> 00:10:22.686 A:middle
Watch apps.

00:10:22.916 --> 00:10:24.266 A:middle
Or embedded frameworks
in your app.

00:10:25.066 --> 00:10:27.586 A:middle
And each of those brings its
own signing requirements.

00:10:28.796 --> 00:10:31.216 A:middle
All this can add up to
a complicated picture,

00:10:31.346 --> 00:10:33.226 A:middle
where signing becomes
a bit of a puzzle.

00:10:34.276 --> 00:10:37.406 A:middle
And fitting all the pieces
together can be pretty

00:10:37.406 --> 00:10:38.326 A:middle
difficult sometimes.

00:10:39.786 --> 00:10:42.986 A:middle
So Xcode for many releases
has provided assistance

00:10:42.986 --> 00:10:43.996 A:middle
to help make this easier.

00:10:45.126 --> 00:10:49.416 A:middle
In Xcode 7, the Fix Issue button
would appear whenever Xcode

00:10:49.416 --> 00:10:53.536 A:middle
detected that something was
wrong with your signing setup.

00:10:53.696 --> 00:10:57.166 A:middle
Now sometimes clicking on Fix
Issue would fix the problem,

00:10:57.406 --> 00:10:59.056 A:middle
and you can return to
developing your app.

00:10:59.756 --> 00:11:01.776 A:middle
But a lot of the times it
wouldn't fix the problem.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:10:59.756 --> 00:11:01.776 A:middle
But a lot of the times it
wouldn't fix the problem.

00:11:01.776 --> 00:11:04.146 A:middle
Or you had to click
it multiple times.

00:11:04.986 --> 00:11:08.466 A:middle
And in all cases, Xcode
wasn't very communicative

00:11:08.466 --> 00:11:09.866 A:middle
about what the issue was.

00:11:11.056 --> 00:11:13.066 A:middle
What it did when you
clicked Fix Issue, and why.

00:11:13.766 --> 00:11:16.046 A:middle
And really, if Xcode knew
how to solve the problem,

00:11:16.546 --> 00:11:18.586 A:middle
why did it need to interrupt
your development workflow

00:11:18.586 --> 00:11:21.076 A:middle
and make you click a button?

00:11:21.196 --> 00:11:24.196 A:middle
Interacting with signing
in Xcode 7 often felt

00:11:24.196 --> 00:11:25.966 A:middle
like you were talking
to a black box.

00:11:25.966 --> 00:11:28.926 A:middle
You couldn't see inside, but you
could mash the red panic button

00:11:28.926 --> 00:11:29.956 A:middle
whenever you got frustrated.

00:11:30.706 --> 00:11:32.606 A:middle
So that didn't work
out very well.

00:11:33.126 --> 00:11:35.796 A:middle
And in Xcode 8 we've gotten
rid of the Fix Issue button.

00:11:35.796 --> 00:11:38.286 A:middle
But we've also done a lot more.

00:11:39.516 --> 00:11:42.896 A:middle
[ Applause ]

00:11:43.396 --> 00:11:46.006 A:middle
We fully redesigned how
signing works in Xcode 8.

00:11:46.986 --> 00:11:48.856 A:middle
There's a brand new
signing infrastructure

00:11:49.456 --> 00:11:51.876 A:middle
which is much faster and
more reliable than before.

00:11:53.116 --> 00:11:55.346 A:middle
On top of that, we
built new workflows,

00:11:55.676 --> 00:11:58.056 A:middle
and a new user interface
in the General tab.

00:11:58.406 --> 00:12:01.736 A:middle
So you can see and manage
your signing settings all


