00:12:01.736 --> 00:12:02.576 A:middle
in one place.

00:12:03.086 --> 00:12:06.696 A:middle
Then we took a look at
how Xcode communicates

00:12:06.696 --> 00:12:08.196 A:middle
with you about signing issues.

00:12:09.586 --> 00:12:12.316 A:middle
A lot of the error messages
were not very actionable

00:12:12.316 --> 00:12:13.066 A:middle
or communicative.

00:12:13.446 --> 00:12:15.366 A:middle
And so we've revised
them all in Xcode8.

00:12:15.816 --> 00:12:17.446 A:middle
So that you see much
more helpful

00:12:17.446 --> 00:12:19.846 A:middle
and actionable information
when something goes wrong.

00:12:21.336 --> 00:12:23.146 A:middle
And for those of you
who are very curious

00:12:23.146 --> 00:12:24.996 A:middle
about what Xcode
does on your behalf

00:12:25.466 --> 00:12:27.016 A:middle
when it fixes a signing problem.

00:12:27.516 --> 00:12:28.866 A:middle
We've added new status
reporting.

00:12:28.866 --> 00:12:31.886 A:middle
So you can always see exactly
what Xcode did and why.

00:12:32.546 --> 00:12:36.426 A:middle
So as Joshua mentioned
at the beginning,

00:12:36.696 --> 00:12:40.356 A:middle
there are two new ways of
working with signing in Xcode 8.

00:12:40.846 --> 00:12:43.176 A:middle
The first one is
automatic signing.

00:12:44.636 --> 00:12:47.396 A:middle
Now automatic signing has
been fully redesigned,

00:12:47.586 --> 00:12:50.316 A:middle
and it takes care of all of
your signing needs for you.

00:12:51.816 --> 00:12:55.416 A:middle
You'll never need to create a
profile, or update your app ID.

00:12:55.646 --> 00:12:57.496 A:middle
And Xcode will do it
all in the background.

00:12:57.656 --> 00:12:59.536 A:middle
So while you're developing
your application,

00:12:59.906 --> 00:13:01.816 A:middle
Xcode will keep your
signing up to date.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:12:59.906 --> 00:13:01.816 A:middle
Xcode will keep your
signing up to date.

00:13:04.906 --> 00:13:06.726 A:middle
For those of you who
want full control

00:13:06.726 --> 00:13:08.336 A:middle
over how your application
is signed,

00:13:08.736 --> 00:13:10.506 A:middle
you can enable customized
signing.

00:13:11.426 --> 00:13:15.046 A:middle
In this mode, Xcode will
never create or modify one

00:13:15.046 --> 00:13:16.526 A:middle
of your provisioning profiles.

00:13:16.906 --> 00:13:18.736 A:middle
And it will never change
your signing settings.

00:13:19.956 --> 00:13:21.606 A:middle
So let's take a look
at how these work

00:13:21.606 --> 00:13:22.576 A:middle
in a little bit more detail.

00:13:22.576 --> 00:13:24.276 A:middle
Starting with automatic signing.

00:13:25.876 --> 00:13:27.826 A:middle
When you create a new project,

00:13:28.246 --> 00:13:30.316 A:middle
automatic signing
will be on by default.

00:13:31.276 --> 00:13:32.856 A:middle
But if you're an
experienced developer,

00:13:32.856 --> 00:13:36.196 A:middle
or you're opening an existing
project, you can enable it

00:13:36.196 --> 00:13:38.646 A:middle
in the General tab in
this new signing UI.

00:13:40.136 --> 00:13:42.236 A:middle
All you have to do
is check the box.

00:13:43.616 --> 00:13:46.006 A:middle
And then tell Xcode
your development team.

00:13:47.196 --> 00:13:50.346 A:middle
From that point on, Xcode will
take care of creating profiles

00:13:50.626 --> 00:13:52.096 A:middle
and signing certificates
for you.

00:13:52.356 --> 00:13:54.806 A:middle
And it will even show you
the profile and certificate

00:13:54.806 --> 00:13:57.626 A:middle
that will be used when
you build your app.

00:13:58.676 --> 00:14:01.256 A:middle
So what sorts of things will
automatic signing do for you?


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:13:58.676 --> 00:14:01.256 A:middle
So what sorts of things will
automatic signing do for you?

00:14:01.686 --> 00:14:04.686 A:middle
Well, it will create your
signing certificates.

00:14:05.296 --> 00:14:06.766 A:middle
So if you're developing
an iOS app,

00:14:07.076 --> 00:14:09.696 A:middle
it'll create an iOS
development certificate for you.

00:14:09.696 --> 00:14:14.206 A:middle
It will also create and update
your app ID's and profiles.

00:14:14.616 --> 00:14:15.256 A:middle
And it does this

00:14:15.256 --> 00:14:17.926 A:middle
in the background while you're
working on your application.

00:14:18.176 --> 00:14:19.976 A:middle
So you can stay focused
on developments.

00:14:20.486 --> 00:14:24.286 A:middle
But there are still
some instances

00:14:24.406 --> 00:14:25.806 A:middle
where Xcode 8 will prompt you.

00:14:26.286 --> 00:14:29.186 A:middle
In particular, when you connect
a new device to your Mac.

00:14:30.196 --> 00:14:31.826 A:middle
One that's not already
registered

00:14:31.826 --> 00:14:32.876 A:middle
on your development team.

00:14:33.756 --> 00:14:35.926 A:middle
Xcode will ask you
before it registers it.

00:14:36.376 --> 00:14:38.816 A:middle
Because we know device limits
are finite, and you want

00:14:38.816 --> 00:14:40.896 A:middle
to have full control over
how those are allocated.

00:14:41.376 --> 00:14:46.166 A:middle
And finally, if you're
curious about what Xcode does

00:14:46.166 --> 00:14:47.676 A:middle
on your behalf in
the background,

00:14:48.056 --> 00:14:49.336 A:middle
you can view the signing report

00:14:50.216 --> 00:14:51.946 A:middle
to see exactly what
Xcode did, and why.

