There's a new build setting

00:21:53.876 --> 00:21:56.736 A:middle
in Xcode 8 called
Provisioning Profile Specifier.

00:21:57.736 --> 00:22:00.196 A:middle
And what this does is it
references your profiles


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:21:57.736 --> 00:22:00.196 A:middle
And what this does is it
references your profiles

00:22:00.196 --> 00:22:00.836 A:middle
by name.

00:22:02.076 --> 00:22:05.816 A:middle
Now the reason this is a
big deal is because prior

00:22:05.816 --> 00:22:08.516 A:middle
to Xcode 8, Xcode would
reference your profiles

00:22:08.516 --> 00:22:10.296 A:middle
by their unique ID.

00:22:10.696 --> 00:22:12.426 A:middle
Whenever a new developer
joined your team,

00:22:12.426 --> 00:22:13.696 A:middle
or you added a new device,

00:22:14.146 --> 00:22:16.736 A:middle
you'd need to generate a
new version of your profile.

00:22:16.736 --> 00:22:19.246 A:middle
And when you did that,
you'd get a new unique ID.

00:22:19.536 --> 00:22:21.466 A:middle
So then you'd need to
update your project.

00:22:22.756 --> 00:22:26.376 A:middle
Well, now in Xcode 8, since
we reference profiles by name,

00:22:26.826 --> 00:22:29.216 A:middle
all you need to do is
generate a new profile,

00:22:29.676 --> 00:22:31.586 A:middle
and Xcode will automatically
pick it up.

00:22:31.586 --> 00:22:36.326 A:middle
You don't need to update your
project [applause] thank you.

