00:28:58.296 --> 00:29:00.836 A:middle
The first thing is,
use automatic.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:28:58.296 --> 00:29:00.836 A:middle
The first thing is,
use automatic.

00:29:01.186 --> 00:29:04.756 A:middle
Automatic is designed to make
your life as easy as possible.

00:29:05.296 --> 00:29:07.436 A:middle
And it works great

00:29:07.436 --> 00:29:10.756 A:middle
with individual developers,
or large teams.

00:29:11.166 --> 00:29:14.526 A:middle
So you should add all of the
developers that work on your app

00:29:14.966 --> 00:29:16.766 A:middle
to your development team.

00:29:17.456 --> 00:29:21.246 A:middle
You should use the Capabilities
tab to manage entitlements.

00:29:21.496 --> 00:29:23.716 A:middle
So you can avoid visiting
the developer website

00:29:23.826 --> 00:29:26.426 A:middle
to configure things
like iCloud containers.

00:29:27.136 --> 00:29:33.296 A:middle
If you use customized signing,
don't set code sign identity.

00:29:33.846 --> 00:29:36.036 A:middle
You have a specific
signing certificate

00:29:36.146 --> 00:29:37.756 A:middle
that is linked to your account.

00:29:38.306 --> 00:29:41.266 A:middle
So if you set this to your
particular signing cert

00:29:41.486 --> 00:29:43.186 A:middle
and someone else
pulls your project,

00:29:43.746 --> 00:29:44.946 A:middle
they won't be able to build.

00:29:45.356 --> 00:29:47.516 A:middle
So you should leave that
with the default value.

00:29:48.856 --> 00:29:51.616 A:middle
Instead of visiting the
Build Settings Editor,

00:29:51.836 --> 00:29:53.116 A:middle
you should use the new UI

00:29:53.296 --> 00:29:55.456 A:middle
in the General tab
of the Target Editor.

00:29:56.186 --> 00:29:59.936 A:middle
This allows you to see more
information about the profile.

00:29:59.936 --> 00:30:04.736 A:middle
And it also correctly sets
the profile specifier by name,


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:29:59.936 --> 00:30:04.736 A:middle
And it also correctly sets
the profile specifier by name,

00:30:05.016 --> 00:30:07.096 A:middle
so you can avoid churn
in your projects.

00:30:07.656 --> 00:30:11.306 A:middle
You should also use
the Capabilities tab

00:30:11.506 --> 00:30:14.566 A:middle
in Customized Signing Mode to
manage your entitlements PLIST.

00:30:15.036 --> 00:30:19.526 A:middle
And if you use development
signing for all

00:30:19.526 --> 00:30:23.276 A:middle
of your project's configuration,
you should try out automatic.

00:30:23.836 --> 00:30:26.606 A:middle
When you get back to your
Mac, go check that checkbox

00:30:26.606 --> 00:30:30.966 A:middle
in the target editor
and try it out.

00:30:31.726 --> 00:30:34.436 A:middle
When it comes to
distributing your app,

00:30:34.436 --> 00:30:37.306 A:middle
Xcode has a dedicated
workflow for this.

00:30:37.646 --> 00:30:40.576 A:middle
And it's based around
building an archive.

00:30:42.246 --> 00:30:44.396 A:middle
Archives contain a
copy of your app.

00:30:45.736 --> 00:30:47.306 A:middle
And it's important to note

00:30:47.306 --> 00:30:49.306 A:middle
that you should use
development signing.

00:30:50.316 --> 00:30:53.426 A:middle
If you sign your app with
a distribution certificate,

00:30:53.826 --> 00:30:56.296 A:middle
you won't be able to
test the exact bits

00:30:56.296 --> 00:30:57.666 A:middle
that you were trying to develop.

00:30:58.386 --> 00:31:00.746 A:middle
So this should be
development signed.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:30:58.386 --> 00:31:00.746 A:middle
So this should be
development signed.

00:31:01.376 --> 00:31:03.636 A:middle
And when it comes time
to distribute that,

00:31:03.936 --> 00:31:05.276 A:middle
when you use the organizer,

00:31:05.626 --> 00:31:09.696 A:middle
Xcode will resign the app using
your development certificate

00:31:09.826 --> 00:31:11.466 A:middle
and provisioning profiles.

00:31:12.356 --> 00:31:14.656 A:middle
